Title: Tree Borrows
Description:
Tree Borrows is a proposed alternative to Stacked
Borrows that fulfills the same role: to define the runtime
requiremenst of the aliasing constraints that pointers must follow.
Execution paths that violate these constraints are declared to contain
Undefined Behavior (UB) and can be assumed by the compiler to never
occur. This enables optimizations that would otherwise be unsound in the
presence of unsafe code.
